The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically the minimum $k$-cut problem. This problem is related to graph connectivity and partitioning, which are central topics in computer science. The paper uses combinatorial techniques and graph theory to develop a faster algorithm for the problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves complexity analysis and lower bounds, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
